{
    "id": "478",
    "title": "Crohn's Disease Activity Index (CDAI)",
    "desc": "The Crohn's Disease Activity Index (CDAI) determines the current severity of Crohn’s disease.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1248701",
                "text": "Best WR, Becktel JM, Singleton JW, Kern F Jr. Development of a Crohn's disease activity index. National Cooperative Crohn's Disease Study. Gastroenterology. 1976 Mar;70(3):439-44."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p>Addition of the selected points.</p>",
        "facts": "<div class=\"table-responsive\">\n<table class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Criteria</th>\n<th>Amount</th>\n<th>Answer</th>\n<th>Multiplier</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Number<br>of<br>liquid<br>stools</td>\n<td>Sum, past 7 days</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&times;2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Abdominal<br>pain</td>\n<td>Average daily rating &times; 7</td>\n<td>0 = None<br>1 = Mild<br>2 = Moderate<br>3 = Severe</td>\n<td>&times;5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>General<br>well-being</td>\n<td>Average daily rating &times; 7</td>\n<td>0 = Generally well<br>1 = Slightly under par<br>2 = Poor<br>3 = Very poor<br>4 = Terrible</td>\n<td>&times;7</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Extra-<br>intestinal/<br>physical complaints*</td>\n<td>Number of complications listed</td>\n<td>0 = No,<br>1 = Yes*</td>\n<td>&times;20</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Antidiarrheal drugs</td>\n<td>Use in the previous 7 days</td>\n<td>0 = No<br>1 = Yes</td>\n<td>&times;30</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Abdominal mass</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>0 = No<br>2 = Questionable,<br>5 = Definite</td>\n<td>&times;10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hematocrit</td>\n<td>Expected &ndash; observed hematocrit</td>\n<td>Men: 47% observed,<br>Women: 42% observed</td>\n<td>&times;6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Body weight</td>\n<td>% below&nbsp;ideal weight</td>\n<td>(Ideal - observed) / ideal &times; 100</td>\n<td>&times;1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*Arthritis/arthralgia, mucocutaneous lesions (e.g. erythema nodosum, aphthous ulcers), iritis/uveitis, anal disease (fissure, fistula, etc), external fistula (enterocutaneous, vesicle, vaginal, etc), fever over 37.8&deg;C</p>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Score interpretation:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>CDAI &lt;150 is a marker of remission of Crohn&rsquo;s disease.</li>\n<li>CDAI &gt;450 is a marker of severe Crohn's disease.</li>\n</ul>",
